	<text>
		<body>
			<p>“I have the honor to refer to paragraph 1, section c, of my telegram No. 39, <date when="1938-03-29">March 29, 1938</date>, 5 p.m.,
				regarding a proposed <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-950" type="subject">bill</term> to limit ritual
				slaughter in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName> and to report that a new <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-950" type="subject">bill</term> calling for a gradual diminution of <term
					ref="#ehri_dr_ritual_slaughter">ritual slaughter</term> over the next three years has just passed the Committee of the <orgName
					ref="#ehri_dr_sejm">Sejm</orgName> and awaits presentation to that body as a whole. […]</p>
			<p>In discussing with the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-895" type="subject">leaders of various Jewish
					groups</term> their reactions, I gained the impression that it is mainly the orthodox, and even amongst their number the more
				strictly religious, who, from a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-726" type="subject">religious
					angle</term> are seriously concerned over the prospect of eventually doing away with <term ref="#ehri_dr_ritual_slaughter">ritual
					slaughter</term>. Others, such as the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-907" type="subject"
					>Zionists</term>, and the Zionist Revisionists, and particularly the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1203" type="subject">youth</term> thereof, are less concerned by the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-950" type="subject">bill’s</term> potential effect on <term
					ref="#ehri_dr_ritual_slaughter">ritual slaughter</term> than by the prospect of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-950" type="subject">bill’s</term> presaging further <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-337" type="subject">anti-Semitic measures</term>. One prominent member of
				the Zionist Revisionist inner circles imparted his opinion that the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-950"
					type="subject">bill</term> was aimed mainly as <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-342" type="subject"
					>propaganda</term> to force the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> of
				all categories in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName> to unite in support of
				the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-948" type="subject">Government</term> search for a solution of the
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-351" type="subject">Jewish problem</term>, mainly in terms of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-203" type="subject">emigration</term>. […]</p>
			<p>My own observation led me to believe that contributing to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-950"
					type="subject">bill’s</term> proposal there are the following military and social aspects: military, in that the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1077" type="subject">Army’s</term> long-range program envisages the
				eventual centralization of meat control and refrigeration to meet emergency periods; and socially, in that the racial <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Polish</placeName> peasant wants to replace the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jew</term> in the meat <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-924" type="subject">business</term>. As to the prospects of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-950" type="subject">bill’s</term> amendment, this, in my opinion, will
				depend largely upon the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-948" type="subject">Government’s</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-815" type="subject">attitude</term> in general towards the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-351" type="subject">Jewish question</term>. At the moment, I do not look
				for the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-950" type="subject">bill</term> to be rejected.”</p>
